<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Chen's blog (ubuntu)</title><link>http://blog.binchen.org/</link><description></description><atom:link href="http://blog.binchen.org/categories/ubuntu.xml" type="application/rss+xml" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 12 Aug 2016 06:34:19 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>https://getnikola.com/</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>How to install Emacs source code under Ubuntu</title><link>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/how-to-install-emacs-source-code-under-ubuntu.html</link><dc:creator>Chen Bin</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Only one command: &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;pre class="prettyprint "&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sudo apt-get install emacs24-el&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;p&gt; How I locate that package emacs24-el: &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;pre class="prettyprint "&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sudo apt-get install apt-file;sudo apt-file update;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;apt-file search help.el.gz&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;p&gt; BTW, I assign hot key "C-h C-f" to command "find-fuction" which "Find the definition of the FUNCTION near point". &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description><category>emacs</category><category>en</category><category>ubuntu</category><guid>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/how-to-install-emacs-source-code-under-ubuntu.html</guid><pubDate>Mon, 12 Aug 2013 09:44:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>